22/02/2005
PROMACHONAS, Greece -- Bulgarian Transport and Communications Minister Nikolay Vassilev and his Greek counterpart, Michalis Liapis, signed a co-operation protocol Monday (21 February) on improving the road and railway infrastructure that links the two countries.
The officials inspected border facilities at Kulata in Bulgaria and Promachonas in Greece, agreeing on concrete measures such as the immediate launch of a luxury train connection between Sofia and Thessaloniki.
(bTV, ANA - 21/02/05)
